Avocado-vt inside the container

That a simple way to use avocado-vt in the system, when you are worried
about breaking the system or you wish to test a new version of the
framework.

How to use avocado-vt inside the container:
First you need clone the dockerfile Fedora.dockerfile
On the Fedora 31 podman is a default instead docker
Build an image with provided avocado version:

# podman build --build-arg avocado_version=73.0 -t avocado-vt -f Fedora.dockerfile .

   It can be change and provide next args:
            avocado_version
            --build-arg TAG_VERSION=30

To run tests need to add a list of volumes from the system and the list
will be depends-on which test you want to run:
avocado_command - test command
# podman run --name avocado-vt --network host --rm --privileged -v "/usr/bin/qemu-img:/usr/bin/qemu-img" \
      -v "/usr/bin/qemu-io:/usr/bin/qemu-io" -v "/usr/libexec/qemu-kvm:/usr/libexec/qemu-kvm" -v "/root/avocado:/root/avocado" \
      -v "/var/lib/avocado:/var/lib/avocado" -v "/var/log:/var/log" -v "/usr/lib64/qemu-kvm:/usr/lib64/qemu-kvm" -v \
       "/usr/share/qemu-kvm:/usr/share/qemu-kvm" -v "/usr/share/ipxe.efi:/usr/share/ipxe.efi" \
      -i -t localhost/avocado-vt avocado {{ avocado_command }}

